 offenders]]\n[[Category:Female murder victims]]\n[[Category:Formerly missing people found dead]]\n[[Category:History of Cambridgeshire]]\n[[Category:Missing person cases in England]]\n[[Category:Murder in Cambridgeshire]]\n[[Category:Murdered English children]]\n[[Category:Prisoners sentenced to life imprisonment by England and Wales]]\n[[Category:Soham]]\n[[Category:Violence against children]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:enamel\u2192enamel paint,ladies' man\u2192wikt:lady's man", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soham_murders"}
{"title_page": "Jawani Phir Nahi Ani", "text_new": "{{short description|2015 film by Nadeem Baig}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use Pakistani English|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Jawani Phir Nahi Ani\n| image          = Jawani Phir Nahi Ani.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| film name      = {{Infobox name module|ur|{{Nq|\u062c\u0648\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u067e\u06be\u0631 \u0646\u06c1\u06cc\u06ba \u0622\u0646\u06cc}}}}\n| director       = [[Nadeem Baig (director)|Nadeem Baig]]\n| producer       = [[Humayun Saeed]]<br>[[Salman Iqbal]]<br>Shahzad Nasib<br>Jarjees Seja\n| writer         = [[Vasay Chaudhry]]\n| screenplay     = \n| story          = \n| based on       = <!-- {{based on|title of the original work|writer of the original work}} -->\n| starring       = <!-- PLEASE DONT ADD/REMOVE THESE CREDITS -->{{plainlist|\n* [[Humayun Saeed]]\n* [[Hamza Ali Abbasi]]\n* [[Ahmad Ali Butt]]\n* [[Vasay Chaudhry]]\n* [[Ayesha Khan]]\n* [[Sarwat Gillani]]\n* [[Uzma Khan]]\n* [[Mehwish Hayat]]\n* [[Sohai Ali Abro]]\n* [[Ismail Tara]]\n* [[Jawed Sheikh]] \n* [[Bushra Ansari]]\n* [[Farhan Ally Agha]]\n}}<!-- PLEASE DONT ADD/REMOVE THESE CREDITS -->\n| narrator       = <!-- or: |narrators = -->\n| music          = [[Ahmad Ali Butt]]<br>[[Shani Arshad]]<br>[[Sahir Ali Bagga]]\n| cinematography = Mujahid Raza\n| editing        = Rizwan AQ\n| studio         = [[Six Sigma Plus]]\n| distributor    = [[ARY Films]]\n| released       = {{film date|2015|09|25|df=y|worldwide}}\n| runtime        = 156 minutes\n| country        = [[Pakistan]]\n| language       = [[Urdu]]\n| budget         = {{PKR|85 million}}\n| gross          = {{PKR|494.4 million}}<ref name=\"JPNA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lollywoodonline.com/p/highest-grosser.html?m=1|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani total collection|work=Box Office Pakistan|accessdate=23 August 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani''''' ({{lit|Youth won't come again}}), sometimes abbreviated as '''''JPNA''''' is a 2015 [[Cinema of Pakistan|Pakistani]] [[Adventure film|adventure]] [[comedy film]] directed by [[Nadeem Baig (director)|Nadeem Baig]]. It was co-produced by [[Humayun Saeed]], Salman Iqbal and Shahzad Nasib at Saeed's production house, [[Six Sigma Plus]]. It is the first installment in the [[Jawani Phir Nahi Ani (film series)|''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'' film series]], The film stars [[Humayun Saeed]], [[Hamza Ali Abbasi]], [[Ahmad Ali Butt]], [[Vasay Chaudhry]], [[Mehwish Hayat]] and [[Sohai Ali Abro]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1144201|title=Humayun Saeed to release new film 'Jawani Phir Nahi Aani'|work=[[DAWN.com]]|publisher=Anum Rehman|accessdate=29 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Humayun Saeed's upcoming film \u2018Jawani Phir Nahi Aani\u2019 eagerly awaited|url=http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/09-Dec-2014/humayun-saeed-s-upcoming-film-jawani-phir-nahi-aani-eagerly-awaited|accessdate=29 March 2015|work=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141209063757/http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/09-Dec-2014/humayun-saeed-s-upcoming-film-jawani-phir-nahi-aani-eagerly-awaited|archive-date=9 December 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The supporting cast includes [[Jawed Sheikh]], [[Ismail Tara]], [[Bushra Ansari]], [[Ayesha Khan]], [[Sarwat Gilani|Sarwat Gillani]] and [[Uzma Khan]]. The film is about a single man who is a divorce lawyer. He takes his three married friends on a trip to help them escape their wives.\n\nThe film was shot in various locations in Abbottabad including [[Bangkok]], [[Pattaya]] and [[Coral Island]].<ref name=\"pakistantoday.com.pk\">{{cite web|title=Humayun Saeed's film shooting finished|url=http://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2015/06/15/entertainment/humayun-saeeds-jawani-phir-nahi-ani-completes-filming/|website=Pakistan Today|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref> A few scenes were shot in [[Karachi]]. On 5 June 2020 the film wrapped and post-production began.The film was released on [[Eid al-Adha]], 25 September 2015. It received positive reviews from critics and grossed {{PKR|494 million}} worldwide, becoming the [[Highest grossing Pakistani films|highest grossing Pakistani film]] to that date, breaking the record of ''[[Waar (2013 film)|Waar]]'' (2013). This record was then broken by ''[[Punjab Nahi Jaungi]]'' (2017).<ref name=\"JPNA\"/> It is currently the [[Highest-grossing Pakistani films|third-highest-grossing Pakistani film]].\n\nA sequel, ''[[Jawani Phir Nahi Ani 2]]'', was released on August 22, 2018 with Baig returning as director.\n\n== Plot ==\nThree childhood friends, Saif ([[Hamza Ali Abbasi]]), Sheikh ([[Vasay Chaudhry]]) and Pervez ([[Ahmad Ali Butt]]), have settled down in married life but are afraid of their wives. Their friend Sherry ([[Humayun Saeed]]), a divorce lawyer, returns to Pakistan from the United States and finds that all his friends are in miserable marriages. Sherry treats the wives well so that they allow their husbands to accompany Sherry on a road trip to [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]]. Sherry actually plans to take the men to [[Bangkok]] to add excitement to their lives.\n\nIn Bangkok, Sherry meets a girl named Marina ([[Mehwish Hayat]]) and they fall in love. However, when Sherry learns that Marina is the daughter of a crime boss named Bichi Don ([[Ismail Tara]]), he wants to leave Bangkok to get away from Marina.\n\nThe men's wives, having learnt of the deception, arrive at the Bangkok hotel where the group are staying. Pervez tries to commit suicide by jumping off the hotel but is saved when he lands in a swimming pool. Sherry tells the wives that the trip was the men's idea and not his. The wives demand divorces from their husbands, saying they can no longer trust them.\n\nA few months pass and the three friends learn that Sherry is to marry Zoya ([[Sohai Ali Abro]]). She is the daughter of Mehboob Khan ([[Javed Sheikh]]), a billionaire in Lahore. Zoya is the quintessential nouveau riche kid, who insists on speaking with a strong American-English accent and abbreviates expressions like \"OMG\" (Oh my God) and \"MA\" ([[Mashallah|Masha'Allah]]). She enjoys spending her father's money carelessly. Zoya's mother ([[Bushra Ansari]]), worries about her daughter's attitude.\n\nWhen the three friends arrive at Sherry's wedding, he asks them not to tell Zoya and her family about Marina. Bichi Don arrives at the wedding and introduces himself as \"Ya Sheikh\", a friend of Mehboob Khan. Sherry tells everyone that his friend, Saif's nickname is also Sherry. The farce is that no one knows which Sherry anyone is talking about.\n\nTwo days before the marriage, Marina arrives. Sherry wants Marina's father to reject him as a potential son-in-law, so he pretends to be a homosexual. The ploy works and Marina and her father leave, only to return on the day of the wedding. Mehboob Khan and Marina's father, (Ya Sheikh) argue about Sherry and this results in both men rejecting Sherry as a potential son-in-law. The story ends when the three friends patch things up with their wives and Sherry asks for Marina's hand in marriage.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Humayun Saeed]] as Shereyar a.k.a Sherry\n* [[Hamza Ali Abbasi]] as Saif Ahmed a.k.a Saif/Sherry\n* [[Ahmad Ali Butt]] as Parvez (Pipi)\n* [[Vasay Chaudhry]] as Sheikh\n* [[Ayesha Khan]] as Kubra (Saif's wife) \n* [[Sohai Ali Abro]] as Zoya \n* [[Mehwish Hayat]] as Marina \n* [[Sarwat Gillani]] as Gul (Sheikh's wife)\n* [[Uzma Khan]] as Lubna (Parvez's wife)\n* [[Jawed Sheikh]] as Mehboob Khan (Zoya's father)\n* [[Bushra Ansari]] as Jabbo (Zoya's mother)\n* [[Ismail Tara]] as Don / Yaa Sheikh (Marina's father)\n* Bashar Amir Shafi as Pipi's son (child artist)\n\n===Special Appearance===\n* [[Gohar Rasheed]] as XYZ (fashion designer)\n* [[Farhan Ally Agha]] as Sherry's father\n* [[Yasra Rizvi]] as Sherry's mother\n* Naveed Raza as Lawyer\n* [[Zainab Qayyum]] as Lawyer\n* [[Ali Kazmi]] as Dr. Aamir Liaquat Khan\n* [[Fahad Mustafa]] as Himself \n* Zainab Jamil as Charity\n* [[Bilal Lashari]] as Police officer\n* Wajid Khan as Stylist\n* [[Saife Hassan]] as Lawyer \n* [[Adnan Siddiqui]] as Himself (in picture) \n* [[Shakeel Hussain Khan]] as a caller \n* Viktor Krav as Gangster\n\n== Production ==\n\n===Filming===\nThe film was shot in various locations in [[Thailand]] including [[Bangkok]], [[Pattaya]] and [[Coral Island]].<ref name=\"pakistantoday.com.pk\"/> A few scenes were shot in [[Karachi]]. On 5 June 2015, the film wrapped and post-production began.\n{{Quotebox\n|quote= \"...The final day of the shoot was quite tough as it was very hot in Karachi so it was a relief that it went smoothly. Hamza Ali Abbasi, Ahmed Butt, Vasay Chaudhry and I also got our faces clean-shaved for the final portion which was quite fun. The entire team including cast members, the crew and myself are very happy with the final results and excited to see the feedback from audiences now.\"\n|source= \u2014[[Humayun Saeed]] speaking about last shot of film.<ref>{{cite news|title=It's a wrap for 'Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/904085/its-a-wrap-for-jawani-phir-nahi-ani/|accessdate=17 June 2015|work=[[The Express Tribune]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Humayun Saeed completes filming \u2018Jawani Phir Nahi Ani\u2019 |url=http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/16-Jun-2015/humayun-saeed-completes-filming-jawani-phir-nahi-ani |accessdate=17 June 2015 |work=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150617123457/http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/16-Jun-2015/humayun-saeed-completes-filming-jawani-phir-nahi-ani |archivedate=17 June 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=It's a wrap for Jawaani Phir Nahi Aani!|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1188366|accessdate=17 June 2015|work=[[DAWN.com]]}}</ref>\n|align=center\n|width=90%\n}}\n\n===Marketing===\nOn 31 March 2015,  a [[teaser campaign|teaser]] was released by [[ARY Films]] on [[ARY Digital Network]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u2018Jawani Phir Nahi Aani\u2019 teaser trailer released|url=http://www.brecorder.com/arts-a-leisure/50-movies/236127-\u2018jawani-phir-nahi-aani\u2019-teaser-trailer-released.html|accessdate=1 April 2015|work=[[Business Recorder]]|publisher=Asfia Afzal}}</ref> On 15 August 2015, the trailer was released.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani's trailer creates a buzz on social media|url=http://www.thenewstribe.com/2015/08/15/jawani-phir-nahi-anis-trailer-creates-a-buzz-on-social-media/|accessdate=16 August 2015|work=The News Tribe}}</ref> The video promotion of one of the movie's [[soundtrack]]s, ''Jalwa'' (sung by Sana Zulfiqar and [[Sahir Ali Bagga]]) was released on 26 August 2015. Five theatrical posters of the film, featuring the main cast, were released at [[ARY Films]]' official [[Facebook]] page on 29 August 2015. Two days later, another soundtrack, ''Khul Jaye Botal'' was released on television channels on the ARY Digital Network. On 18 September 2015, a second trailer (edited by [[Bilal Lashari]]) was released. The cast appeared on several morning television shows including ''Morning with Juggan'' on 18 September 2015 and ''Good Morning Pakistan'' on [[Eid al-Adha]] (a feast day in Pakistan) to promote their movie.\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe film's music album consists of 6 songs. A soundtrack album was released on [[Saavn]].<ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA soundtrack album|url=http://www.saavn.com/p/album/hindi/Yeh-Jawani-Phir-Nahi-Ani-2015/s5fmG5CpWpg_|website=[[Saavn]]|accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Jawani Phir Nahi Ani<ref>{{Cite web|title = Tamasha (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) on iTunes|url = https://itunes.apple.com/in/album/tamasha-original-motion-picture/id1048180613|publisher = iTunes Store|accessdate = 10 October 2015}}</ref>\n| extra_column    = Singer(s)\n| total_length    = 26 mins\n| title1          = Khul Jaye Botal\n| extra1          = [[Mika Singh]], Tehreem Muniba, [[Shani Haider]]\n| length1         = 04:28\n| title2          = Dance The Party\n| extra2          = [[Ali Gul Pir]], [[Shuja Haider (singer)|Shuja Haider]]\n| length2         = 3:05\n| title3          = Jalwa\n| extra3          = Sana Zulfiqar, [[Sahir Ali Bagga]]\n| length3         = 4:41\n| title4          = Jay Mundiya\n| extra4          = Sana Zulfiqar, Shani Haider\n| length4         = 04:58\n| title5          = Aisa Jorh Hai\n| extra5          = [[Sara Raza Khan]], [[Nabeel Shaukat Ali]]\n| length5         = 05:19\n| title6          = Jawani Phir Nahi Ani\n| extra6          = [[Ahmad Ali Butt]], Faiza Mujahid, [[Noor Jehan|Noor Jahan]]\n| length6         = 03:43\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nOn 19 September 2015, ''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'' premiered in the [[CineStar IMAX Lahore]]. Selected media personnel and celebrities, including [[Mahesh Bhatt]] attended.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Jawani Phir Nahi Ani|url = http://arynews.tv/en/jawani-phir-nahi-ani-premieres-in-lahore-karachi-and-dubai/|website = arynews.tv|accessdate = 2015-11-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = President ARY Network Salman Iqbal, Mahesh Bhatt attend JPNA Lahore premier|url = http://arynews.tv/en/president-ary-network-salman-iqbal-mahesh-bhatt-attend-jpna-lahore-premier/|website = arynews.tv|accessdate = 21 November 2015}}</ref> Another premiere was held on 20 September 2015 at [[Nueplex Cinemas]] in [[Defence Housing Authority, Karachi|DHA, Karachi]].<ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA Karachi premiere|url=http://arynews.tv/en/jawani-phir-nahi-ani-premieres-in-karachi-movie-and-star-studded-event-impresses-all/|website=[[ARY News]]|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref> On 23 September 2015, the film premiered in [[Dubai]] and on 24 September 2015 in [[New York City]]. The [[Chicago]] premiere was held on 26 September 26, 2015 and the [[Los Angeles]] premiere on 27 September 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA all set for a worldwide premier|url=http://www.hipinpakistan.com/news/1147954|website=hip|accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Box office===\nJawani Phir Nahi Ani became the biggest opener for any Pakistani film to that date with collecting \u20a8 2.07 [[crore]], excluding previous day's limited release.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani sets new box office record in Pakistan|url=http://arynews.tv/en/jawani-phir-nahi-ani-sets-new-box-office-record-in-pakistan/|website=[[ARY News]]|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA creates day one record in Pakistan|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5481|website=BoxOfficeDetail|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref> It broke the previous day 1 record of [[Waar]] having \u20a8 1.14 crore.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/619036/waar-beats-box-office-record-with-opening-day-take-of-rs11-4m |title=Waar beats domestic box office record with opening day take of Rs11.4m \u2013 The Express Tribune |work=Express Tribune|date=17 October 2013|accessdate=3 November 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe film collected Rs 2.7 crores on its second day of screening. The total over the first two days was approximately Rs 5 crores.<ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA day two business|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5502|website=BoxOfficeDetail|accessdate=28 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927232416/http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5502|archive-date=27 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> The film collected over Rs 27 crores on the first Sunday of its release.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani on a rampage; makes Rs 27 million on 3rd day of Eid|url=http://arynews.tv/en/jawani-phir-nahi-ani-on-a-rampage-makes-rs-27-million-on-3rd-day-of-eid/|website=[[ARY News]]|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=opening>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani sunday trends: anither record|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5513|website=BoxOfficeDetail|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref> The international earnings on the first weekend was Rs. 2.5 crore.<ref name=overseas_1>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani Worldwide Update :: New Weekend Record|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5551|website=Box Office Detail|accessdate=29 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930031157/http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5551|archive-date=30 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> In its first week, the film grossed over Rs 13.7 crores, breaking a record for the highest domestic first week totals.<ref name=week1>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani Breaks Week One Record In Pakistan|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5569|website=BOD|accessdate=15 October 2015}}</ref> The film's second weekend earnings was Rs 5 crores.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi 12 Days Official Business :: Crosses 20cr|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5638|website=BOD|accessdate=8 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151120214813/http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5638|archive-date=20 November 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> Three weeks after its premier screening, the film had earned Rs 26.5 crores becoming the highest-grossing film in Pakistan.<ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA becomes Pakistan's highest-grossing film|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/972232/jpna-becomes-pakistans-highest-grossing-film/|website=tribune|accessdate=13 October 2015}}</ref> The film had grossed Rs 35.25 crores at the end of its third week, becoming the [[List of highest-grossing Pakistani films|highest-grossing]] Pakistani film worldwide.<ref name=hg>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Breaks All Time Worldwide Record In Pakistan|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5740|website=BOD|accessdate=18 October 2015}}</ref> The film ended its run by collecting Rs 34 crores locally, and Rs 15.44 crores from overseas with a total gross of Rs 49.44 crores the best earning Pakistani film to that date.<ref name=\"JPNA\" />\n\n===Critical reception===\nThe film received positive reviews from critics in Pakistan. Rafay Mahmood of ''[[The Express Tribune]]'' rated the film \"3 out of 5 stars\". He said, \"for all its flaws, ''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'' is a thoroughly entertaining film that will reward you if you don\u2019t think it out too much\". He praised the performances of Saeed and Butt.<ref>{{cite news|title=JPNA: Pointless but very entertaining|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/960929/jpna-pointless-but-very-entertaining/|accessdate=25 September 2015|work=[[The Express Tribune]]|publisher=Rafay Mahmood}}</ref> Asim Malik of [[Daily Times (Pakistan)|''Daily Times'']] wrote, \"this flick is a complete package and every one made sure that the details are covered\".<ref>{{cite news|title=\u2018Jawani Phir Nahi Aani\u2019 delivers what it promises |url=http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/22-Sep-2015/jawani-phir-nahi-aani-delivers-what-it-promises?fb_action_ids=10154170700437506&fb_action_types=og.likes |accessdate=25 September 2015 |work=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]] |publisher=Asim Malik |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925122827/http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/22-Sep-2015/jawani-phir-nahi-aani-delivers-what-it-promises?fb_action_ids=10154170700437506&fb_action_types=og.likes |archivedate=25 September 2015 }}</ref> Salima Feerasta of [[DAWN.com|''DAWN'']] praised Saeed, Butt, Chaudhry, Abbasi and Hayat and said \"despite its flaws, ''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'' is an out-and-out entertainer. An engaging blend of slapstick, spoofs and wit, the film is easy on the eye and an undemanding crowd-pleaser. Definitely worth the price of admission\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Jawani Phir Nahin Aani is a drunk desi uncle on the dance floor|url=http://images.dawn.com/news/1173897/jawani-phir-nahin-aani-is-a-drunk-desi-uncle-on-the-dance-floor-heres-why-you-should-watch-it-now|accessdate=25 September 2015|work=[[DAWN.com]]|publisher=Salima Feerasta}}</ref>\n\nNaveen Qazi of ''Siddy Says'' rated the film as \"4.5 out of 5 stars\". He said, \"staunch religious views and conservative mind-set should be left at home\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Bangkok and brazen banters|url=http://www.siddysays.com/movie-review-jawani-phir-nahi-ani/|website=Siddy Says|publisher=Naveen Qazi|accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref> Momin Ali Munshi of ''Galaxy Lollywood'' rated the film 3.8 out of 5 stars and wrote, \"''Jawani Phir Nahi An''i is an outright commercial film which scores full marks on the entertainment meter\". He praised the performances of Saeed, Butt, Chaudhry, Abro and Gillani.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani ( Review): This laugh out loud riot is the definition of good commercial cinema|url=http://galaxylollywood.com/2015/09/23/jawani-phir-nahi-ani-review-this-laugh-out-loud-riot-is-the-definition-of-good-commercial-cinema/|website=Galaxy Lollywood|publisher=Momin Ali Munshi|accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\nThe film had a television premier on [[Eid al-Fitr]], 4 July 2016, on ARY Digital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/arydigital.tv/videos/world-tv-premiere-of-jawani-phir-nahi-ani-on-1st-day-of-eid-only-on-ary-digital/1284405404904026/|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani - World Tv Premiere|last=ARY Digital|date=2 July 2016|accessdate=4 July 2016|via=Facebook}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\nAt the [[2nd ARY Film Awards]], ''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'' received twenty-nine nominations and won eighteen categories. At the [[15th Lux Style Awards]], the film won two awards from ten nominations.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:99%;\"  <!-- to use sortable requires eliminating all use of rowspan -->\n|-\n! width=\"2%\" scope=\"col\" | Year\n! width=\"20%\" scope=\"col\" | Ceremony\n! width=\"25%\" scope=\"col\" | Category\n! width=\"25%\" scope=\"col\" | Recipient\n! width=\"8%\" scope=\"col\" | Result\n! width=\"2%\" scope=\"col\" | Ref\n|-\n| rowspan=\"39\" | 2016\n| rowspan=\"29\" | [[2nd ARY Film Awards|ARY Film Awards]]\n| colspan=\"2\"  | [[ARY Film Award for Best Film Jury|Best Film Jury]]\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"29\" |<center><ref>{{cite web|title=The nominations for the ARY Film Awards are out, with many stunning debut actors, directors and musicians vying for the coveted awards.|url=http://arynews.tv/en/ary-film-awards-2016-nominations-out/|publisher=[[ARY News]]|date=7 February 2016|accessdate=7 February 2016}}</ref></center> \n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Director Jury|Best Director Jury]]\n| Nadeem Baig\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"  | [[ARY Film Award for Best Film|Best Film]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n| Nadeem Baig\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] \n| [[Humayun Saeed]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2|[[ARY Film Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| [[Mehwish Hayat]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Sohai Ali Abro]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3|[[ARY Film Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]] \n| [[Hamza Ali Abbasi]] \n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Ahmed Ali Butt]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Vasay Chaudhry]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[ARY Film Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| [[Aisha Khan]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Sarwat Gilani]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[ARY Film Award for Best Star Debut Male|Best Star Debut Male]] \n| Ahmed Ali Butt\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Vasay Chaudhry\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Star Debut Female|Best Star Debut Female]]\n| [[Sarwat Gilani]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[ARY Film Award for Best Actor in a Comic Role|Best Actor in a Comic Role]]\n| [[Bushra Ansari]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Ahmed Ali Butt\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Actor in a Negative Role|Best Actor in a Negative Role]]\n| [[Ismail Tara]]\n| {{nom}}\n|- \n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Female Playback Singer|Best Playback Singer - Female]]\n| Sana Zulfiqar\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Male Playback Singer|Best Playback Singer - Male]]\n| [[Mika Singh]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Story|Best Story]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | Vasay Chaudhry\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Dialogue|Best Dialogue]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Original Music|Best Original Music]]\n| [[Shani Arshad]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Action|Best Action]]\n| Viktor Krav \n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Choreography|Best Choreography]]\n| Shabina Khan\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]]\n| Nabila and Jahanzeb Qamar \n| {{won}}\n|- \n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Makeup and Hairstyling|Best Makeup and Hairstyling]]\n| Nabila\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Editing|Best Editing]]\n| Rizwan AQ\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"10\"|[[15th Lux Style Awards]]\n| colspan=\"2\"|Best Film\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"10\"| <center><ref>{{cite news|title=LSA nominations row: Ahmed Ali Butt moved to Best Supporting Actor category|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/1121764/lsa-nominations-row-ahmed-ali-butt-moved-best-supporting-actor-category/|newspaper=[[The Express Tribune]]|date=July 13, 2016|accessdate=July 30, 2016}}</ref></center>\n|-\n| Best Director\n| Nadeem Baig\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Actor\n| Humayun Saeed \n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Actress\n| Mehwish Hayat\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|Best Supporting Actor\n| Javed Sheikh\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Ahmad Ali Butt\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Vasay Chaudhary\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3| Best Supporting Actress\n| Ayesha Khan\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Sarwat Gilani\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Sohai Ali Abro\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==Sequel==\n{{Main|Jawani Phir Nahi Ani 2}}\nBy February 2017 a second ''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'' film was in development with Saeed, Nasib, Iqbal, and Seja returning to produce.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1552836/4|title=Day one on the sets of 'Jawani Phir Nahi Ani 2'|date=8 November 2017|accessdate=9 November 2017|work=The Express Tribune}}</ref> Nadeem Baig returned to direct the film, which began filming November 2017 for an August 2018 release.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1567055/4|title=Final release date of 'Jawani Phir Nahi Ani 2' revealed|date=24 November 2017|accessdate=25 November 2017|work=The Express Tribune}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of directorial debuts]]\n* [[List of Pakistani films of 2015]]\n* [[List of highest-grossing Pakistani films]]\n* [[Jawani Phir Nahi Ani (film series)]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|4692368}}\n\n{{ARY Films}}\n{{Highest-grossing Pakistani films}}\n{{ARY Film Award Best Film}}\n{{ARY Film Award Best Film Jury}}\n\n[[Category:2010s adventure comedy films]]\n[[Category:Pakistani adventure comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films set in Thailand]]\n[[Category:2015 films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Bangkok]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Karachi]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Sahir Ali Bagga]]\n[[Category:Six Sigma Plus]]\n[[Category:2010s buddy comedy films]]\n[[Category:2015 directorial debut films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2015 film by Nadeem Baig}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use Pakistani English|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Jawani Phir Nahi Ani\n| image          = Jawani Phir Nahi Ani.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| film name      = {{Infobox name module|ur|{{Nq|\u062c\u0648\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u067e\u06be\u0631 \u0646\u06c1\u06cc\u06ba \u0622\u0646\u06cc}}}}\n| director       = [[Nadeem Baig (director)|Nadeem Baig]]\n| producer       = [[Humayun Saeed]]<br>[[Salman Iqbal]]<br>Shahzad Nasib<br>Jarjees Seja\n| writer         = [[Vasay Chaudhry]]\n| screenplay     = \n| story          = \n| based on       = <!-- {{based on|title of the original work|writer of the original work}} -->\n| starring       = <!-- PLEASE DONT ADD/REMOVE THESE CREDITS -->{{plainlist|\n* [[Humayun Saeed]]\n* [[Hamza Ali Abbasi]]\n* [[Ahmad Ali Butt]]\n* [[Vasay Chaudhry]]\n* [[Ayesha Khan]]\n* [[Sarwat Gillani]]\n* [[Uzma Khan]]\n* [[Mehwish Hayat]]\n* [[Sohai Ali Abro]]\n* [[Ismail Tara]]\n* [[Jawed Sheikh]] \n* [[Bushra Ansari]]\n* [[Farhan Ally Agha]]\n}}<!-- PLEASE DONT ADD/REMOVE THESE CREDITS -->\n| narrator       = <!-- or: |narrators = -->\n| music          = [[Ahmad Ali Butt]]<br>[[Shani Arshad]]<br>[[Sahir Ali Bagga]]\n| cinematography = Mujahid Raza\n| editing        = Rizwan AQ\n| studio         = [[Six Sigma Plus]]\n| distributor    = [[ARY Films]]\n| released       = {{film date|2015|09|25|df=y|worldwide}}\n| runtime        = 156 minutes\n| country        = [[Pakistan]]\n| language       = [[Urdu]]\n| budget         = {{PKR|85 million}}\n| gross          = {{PKR|494.4 million}}<ref name=\"JPNA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lollywoodonline.com/p/highest-grosser.html?m=1|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani total collection|work=Box Office Pakistan|accessdate=23 August 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani''''' ({{lit|Youth won't come again}}), sometimes abbreviated as '''''JPNA''''' is a 2015 [[Cinema of Pakistan|Pakistani]] [[Adventure film|adventure]] [[comedy film]] directed by [[Nadeem Baig (director)|Nadeem Baig]]. It was co-produced by [[Humayun Saeed]], Salman Iqbal and Shahzad Nasib at Saeed's production house, [[Six Sigma Plus]]. It is the first installment in the [[Jawani Phir Nahi Ani (film series)|''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'' film series]], The film stars [[Humayun Saeed]], [[Hamza Ali Abbasi]], [[Ahmad Ali Butt]], [[Vasay Chaudhry]], [[Mehwish Hayat]] and [[Sohai Ali Abro]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1144201|title=Humayun Saeed to release new film 'Jawani Phir Nahi Aani'|work=[[DAWN.com]]|publisher=Anum Rehman|accessdate=29 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Humayun Saeed's upcoming film \u2018Jawani Phir Nahi Aani\u2019 eagerly awaited|url=http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/09-Dec-2014/humayun-saeed-s-upcoming-film-jawani-phir-nahi-aani-eagerly-awaited|accessdate=29 March 2015|work=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141209063757/http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/09-Dec-2014/humayun-saeed-s-upcoming-film-jawani-phir-nahi-aani-eagerly-awaited|archive-date=9 December 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The supporting cast includes [[Jawed Sheikh]], [[Ismail Tara]], [[Bushra Ansari]], [[Ayesha Khan]], [[Sarwat Gilani|Sarwat Gillani]] and [[Uzma Khan]]. The film is about a single man who is a divorce lawyer. He takes his three married friends on a trip to help them escape their wives.\n\nThe film was shot in various locations in [[Thailand]] including [[Bangkok]], [[Pattaya]] and [[Coral Island]].<ref name=\"pakistantoday.com.pk\">{{cite web|title=Humayun Saeed's film shooting finished|url=http://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2015/06/15/entertainment/humayun-saeeds-jawani-phir-nahi-ani-completes-filming/|website=Pakistan Today|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref> A few scenes were shot in [[Karachi]]. On 5 June 2015, the film wrapped and post-production began.The film was released on [[Eid al-Adha]], 25 September 2015. It received positive reviews from critics and grossed {{PKR|494 million}} worldwide, becoming the [[Highest grossing Pakistani films|highest grossing Pakistani film]] to that date, breaking the record of ''[[Waar (2013 film)|Waar]]'' (2013). This record was then broken by ''[[Punjab Nahi Jaungi]]'' (2017).<ref name=\"JPNA\"/> It is currently the [[Highest-grossing Pakistani films|third-highest-grossing Pakistani film]].\n\nA sequel, ''[[Jawani Phir Nahi Ani 2]]'', was released on August 22, 2018 with Baig returning as director.\n\n== Plot ==\nThree childhood friends, Saif ([[Hamza Ali Abbasi]]), Sheikh ([[Vasay Chaudhry]]) and Pervez ([[Ahmad Ali Butt]]), have settled down in married life but are afraid of their wives. Their friend Sherry ([[Humayun Saeed]]), a divorce lawyer, returns to Pakistan from the United States and finds that all his friends are in miserable marriages. Sherry treats the wives well so that they allow their husbands to accompany Sherry on a road trip to [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]]. Sherry actually plans to take the men to [[Bangkok]] to add excitement to their lives.\n\nIn Bangkok, Sherry meets a girl named Marina ([[Mehwish Hayat]]) and they fall in love. However, when Sherry learns that Marina is the daughter of a crime boss named Bichi Don ([[Ismail Tara]]), he wants to leave Bangkok to get away from Marina.\n\nThe men's wives, having learnt of the deception, arrive at the Bangkok hotel where the group are staying. Pervez tries to commit suicide by jumping off the hotel but is saved when he lands in a swimming pool. Sherry tells the wives that the trip was the men's idea and not his. The wives demand divorces from their husbands, saying they can no longer trust them.\n\nA few months pass and the three friends learn that Sherry is to marry Zoya ([[Sohai Ali Abro]]). She is the daughter of Mehboob Khan ([[Javed Sheikh]]), a billionaire in Lahore. Zoya is the quintessential nouveau riche kid, who insists on speaking with a strong American-English accent and abbreviates expressions like \"OMG\" (Oh my God) and \"MA\" ([[Mashallah|Masha'Allah]]). She enjoys spending her father's money carelessly. Zoya's mother ([[Bushra Ansari]]), worries about her daughter's attitude.\n\nWhen the three friends arrive at Sherry's wedding, he asks them not to tell Zoya and her family about Marina. Bichi Don arrives at the wedding and introduces himself as \"Ya Sheikh\", a friend of Mehboob Khan. Sherry tells everyone that his friend, Saif's nickname is also Sherry. The farce is that no one knows which Sherry anyone is talking about.\n\nTwo days before the marriage, Marina arrives. Sherry wants Marina's father to reject him as a potential son-in-law, so he pretends to be a homosexual. The ploy works and Marina and her father leave, only to return on the day of the wedding. Mehboob Khan and Marina's father, (Ya Sheikh) argue about Sherry and this results in both men rejecting Sherry as a potential son-in-law. The story ends when the three friends patch things up with their wives and Sherry asks for Marina's hand in marriage.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Humayun Saeed]] as Shereyar a.k.a Sherry\n* [[Hamza Ali Abbasi]] as Saif Ahmed a.k.a Saif/Sherry\n* [[Ahmad Ali Butt]] as Parvez (Pipi)\n* [[Vasay Chaudhry]] as Sheikh\n* [[Ayesha Khan]] as Kubra (Saif's wife) \n* [[Sohai Ali Abro]] as Zoya \n* [[Mehwish Hayat]] as Marina \n* [[Sarwat Gillani]] as Gul (Sheikh's wife)\n* [[Uzma Khan]] as Lubna (Parvez's wife)\n* [[Jawed Sheikh]] as Mehboob Khan (Zoya's father)\n* [[Bushra Ansari]] as Jabbo (Zoya's mother)\n* [[Ismail Tara]] as Don / Yaa Sheikh (Marina's father)\n* Bashar Amir Shafi as Pipi's son (child artist)\n\n===Special Appearance===\n* [[Gohar Rasheed]] as XYZ (fashion designer)\n* [[Farhan Ally Agha]] as Sherry's father\n* [[Yasra Rizvi]] as Sherry's mother\n* Naveed Raza as Lawyer\n* [[Zainab Qayyum]] as Lawyer\n* [[Ali Kazmi]] as Dr. Aamir Liaquat Khan\n* [[Fahad Mustafa]] as Himself \n* Zainab Jamil as Charity\n* [[Bilal Lashari]] as Police officer\n* Wajid Khan as Stylist\n* [[Saife Hassan]] as Lawyer \n* [[Adnan Siddiqui]] as Himself (in picture) \n* [[Shakeel Hussain Khan]] as a caller \n* Viktor Krav as Gangster\n\n== Production ==\n\n===Filming===\nThe film was shot in various locations in [[Thailand]] including [[Bangkok]], [[Pattaya]] and [[Coral Island]].<ref name=\"pakistantoday.com.pk\"/> A few scenes were shot in [[Karachi]]. On 5 June 2015, the film wrapped and post-production began.\n{{Quotebox\n|quote= \"...The final day of the shoot was quite tough as it was very hot in Karachi so it was a relief that it went smoothly. Hamza Ali Abbasi, Ahmed Butt, Vasay Chaudhry and I also got our faces clean-shaved for the final portion which was quite fun. The entire team including cast members, the crew and myself are very happy with the final results and excited to see the feedback from audiences now.\"\n|source= \u2014[[Humayun Saeed]] speaking about last shot of film.<ref>{{cite news|title=It's a wrap for 'Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/904085/its-a-wrap-for-jawani-phir-nahi-ani/|accessdate=17 June 2015|work=[[The Express Tribune]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Humayun Saeed completes filming \u2018Jawani Phir Nahi Ani\u2019 |url=http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/16-Jun-2015/humayun-saeed-completes-filming-jawani-phir-nahi-ani |accessdate=17 June 2015 |work=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150617123457/http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/16-Jun-2015/humayun-saeed-completes-filming-jawani-phir-nahi-ani |archivedate=17 June 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=It's a wrap for Jawaani Phir Nahi Aani!|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1188366|accessdate=17 June 2015|work=[[DAWN.com]]}}</ref>\n|align=center\n|width=90%\n}}\n\n===Marketing===\nOn 31 March 2015,  a [[teaser campaign|teaser]] was released by [[ARY Films]] on [[ARY Digital Network]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u2018Jawani Phir Nahi Aani\u2019 teaser trailer released|url=http://www.brecorder.com/arts-a-leisure/50-movies/236127-\u2018jawani-phir-nahi-aani\u2019-teaser-trailer-released.html|accessdate=1 April 2015|work=[[Business Recorder]]|publisher=Asfia Afzal}}</ref> On 15 August 2015, the trailer was released.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani's trailer creates a buzz on social media|url=http://www.thenewstribe.com/2015/08/15/jawani-phir-nahi-anis-trailer-creates-a-buzz-on-social-media/|accessdate=16 August 2015|work=The News Tribe}}</ref> The video promotion of one of the movie's [[soundtrack]]s, ''Jalwa'' (sung by Sana Zulfiqar and [[Sahir Ali Bagga]]) was released on 26 August 2015. Five theatrical posters of the film, featuring the main cast, were released at [[ARY Films]]' official [[Facebook]] page on 29 August 2015. Two days later, another soundtrack, ''Khul Jaye Botal'' was released on television channels on the ARY Digital Network. On 18 September 2015, a second trailer (edited by [[Bilal Lashari]]) was released. The cast appeared on several morning television shows including ''Morning with Juggan'' on 18 September 2015 and ''Good Morning Pakistan'' on [[Eid al-Adha]] (a feast day in Pakistan) to promote their movie.\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe film's music album consists of 6 songs. A soundtrack album was released on [[Saavn]].<ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA soundtrack album|url=http://www.saavn.com/p/album/hindi/Yeh-Jawani-Phir-Nahi-Ani-2015/s5fmG5CpWpg_|website=[[Saavn]]|accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Jawani Phir Nahi Ani<ref>{{Cite web|title = Tamasha (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) on iTunes|url = https://itunes.apple.com/in/album/tamasha-original-motion-picture/id1048180613|publisher = iTunes Store|accessdate = 10 October 2015}}</ref>\n| extra_column    = Singer(s)\n| total_length    = 26 mins\n| title1          = Khul Jaye Botal\n| extra1          = [[Mika Singh]], Tehreem Muniba, [[Shani Haider]]\n| length1         = 04:28\n| title2          = Dance The Party\n| extra2          = [[Ali Gul Pir]], [[Shuja Haider (singer)|Shuja Haider]]\n| length2         = 3:05\n| title3          = Jalwa\n| extra3          = Sana Zulfiqar, [[Sahir Ali Bagga]]\n| length3         = 4:41\n| title4          = Jay Mundiya\n| extra4          = Sana Zulfiqar, Shani Haider\n| length4         = 04:58\n| title5          = Aisa Jorh Hai\n| extra5          = [[Sara Raza Khan]], [[Nabeel Shaukat Ali]]\n| length5         = 05:19\n| title6          = Jawani Phir Nahi Ani\n| extra6          = [[Ahmad Ali Butt]], Faiza Mujahid, [[Noor Jehan|Noor Jahan]]\n| length6         = 03:43\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nOn 19 September 2015, ''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'' premiered in the [[CineStar IMAX Lahore]]. Selected media personnel and celebrities, including [[Mahesh Bhatt]] attended.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Jawani Phir Nahi Ani|url = http://arynews.tv/en/jawani-phir-nahi-ani-premieres-in-lahore-karachi-and-dubai/|website = arynews.tv|accessdate = 2015-11-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = President ARY Network Salman Iqbal, Mahesh Bhatt attend JPNA Lahore premier|url = http://arynews.tv/en/president-ary-network-salman-iqbal-mahesh-bhatt-attend-jpna-lahore-premier/|website = arynews.tv|accessdate = 21 November 2015}}</ref> Another premiere was held on 20 September 2015 at [[Nueplex Cinemas]] in [[Defence Housing Authority, Karachi|DHA, Karachi]].<ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA Karachi premiere|url=http://arynews.tv/en/jawani-phir-nahi-ani-premieres-in-karachi-movie-and-star-studded-event-impresses-all/|website=[[ARY News]]|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref> On 23 September 2015, the film premiered in [[Dubai]] and on 24 September 2015 in [[New York City]]. The [[Chicago]] premiere was held on 26 September 26, 2015 and the [[Los Angeles]] premiere on 27 September 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA all set for a worldwide premier|url=http://www.hipinpakistan.com/news/1147954|website=hip|accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Box office===\nJawani Phir Nahi Ani became the biggest opener for any Pakistani film to that date with collecting \u20a8 2.07 [[crore]], excluding previous day's limited release.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani sets new box office record in Pakistan|url=http://arynews.tv/en/jawani-phir-nahi-ani-sets-new-box-office-record-in-pakistan/|website=[[ARY News]]|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA creates day one record in Pakistan|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5481|website=BoxOfficeDetail|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref> It broke the previous day 1 record of [[Waar]] having \u20a8 1.14 crore.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/619036/waar-beats-box-office-record-with-opening-day-take-of-rs11-4m |title=Waar beats domestic box office record with opening day take of Rs11.4m \u2013 The Express Tribune |work=Express Tribune|date=17 October 2013|accessdate=3 November 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe film collected Rs 2.7 crores on its second day of screening. The total over the first two days was approximately Rs 5 crores.<ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA day two business|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5502|website=BoxOfficeDetail|accessdate=28 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927232416/http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5502|archive-date=27 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> The film collected over Rs 27 crores on the first Sunday of its release.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani on a rampage; makes Rs 27 million on 3rd day of Eid|url=http://arynews.tv/en/jawani-phir-nahi-ani-on-a-rampage-makes-rs-27-million-on-3rd-day-of-eid/|website=[[ARY News]]|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=opening>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani sunday trends: anither record|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5513|website=BoxOfficeDetail|accessdate=28 September 2015}}</ref> The international earnings on the first weekend was Rs. 2.5 crore.<ref name=overseas_1>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani Worldwide Update :: New Weekend Record|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5551|website=Box Office Detail|accessdate=29 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930031157/http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5551|archive-date=30 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> In its first week, the film grossed over Rs 13.7 crores, breaking a record for the highest domestic first week totals.<ref name=week1>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani Breaks Week One Record In Pakistan|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5569|website=BOD|accessdate=15 October 2015}}</ref> The film's second weekend earnings was Rs 5 crores.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi 12 Days Official Business :: Crosses 20cr|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5638|website=BOD|accessdate=8 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151120214813/http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5638|archive-date=20 November 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> Three weeks after its premier screening, the film had earned Rs 26.5 crores becoming the highest-grossing film in Pakistan.<ref>{{cite web|title=JPNA becomes Pakistan's highest-grossing film|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/972232/jpna-becomes-pakistans-highest-grossing-film/|website=tribune|accessdate=13 October 2015}}</ref> The film had grossed Rs 35.25 crores at the end of its third week, becoming the [[List of highest-grossing Pakistani films|highest-grossing]] Pakistani film worldwide.<ref name=hg>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Breaks All Time Worldwide Record In Pakistan|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=5740|website=BOD|accessdate=18 October 2015}}</ref> The film ended its run by collecting Rs 34 crores locally, and Rs 15.44 crores from overseas with a total gross of Rs 49.44 crores the best earning Pakistani film to that date.<ref name=\"JPNA\" />\n\n===Critical reception===\nThe film received positive reviews from critics in Pakistan. Rafay Mahmood of ''[[The Express Tribune]]'' rated the film \"3 out of 5 stars\". He said, \"for all its flaws, ''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'' is a thoroughly entertaining film that will reward you if you don\u2019t think it out too much\". He praised the performances of Saeed and Butt.<ref>{{cite news|title=JPNA: Pointless but very entertaining|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/960929/jpna-pointless-but-very-entertaining/|accessdate=25 September 2015|work=[[The Express Tribune]]|publisher=Rafay Mahmood}}</ref> Asim Malik of [[Daily Times (Pakistan)|''Daily Times'']] wrote, \"this flick is a complete package and every one made sure that the details are covered\".<ref>{{cite news|title=\u2018Jawani Phir Nahi Aani\u2019 delivers what it promises |url=http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/22-Sep-2015/jawani-phir-nahi-aani-delivers-what-it-promises?fb_action_ids=10154170700437506&fb_action_types=og.likes |accessdate=25 September 2015 |work=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]] |publisher=Asim Malik |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925122827/http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/entertainment/22-Sep-2015/jawani-phir-nahi-aani-delivers-what-it-promises?fb_action_ids=10154170700437506&fb_action_types=og.likes |archivedate=25 September 2015 }}</ref> Salima Feerasta of [[DAWN.com|''DAWN'']] praised Saeed, Butt, Chaudhry, Abbasi and Hayat and said \"despite its flaws, ''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'' is an out-and-out entertainer. An engaging blend of slapstick, spoofs and wit, the film is easy on the eye and an undemanding crowd-pleaser. Definitely worth the price of admission\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Jawani Phir Nahin Aani is a drunk desi uncle on the dance floor|url=http://images.dawn.com/news/1173897/jawani-phir-nahin-aani-is-a-drunk-desi-uncle-on-the-dance-floor-heres-why-you-should-watch-it-now|accessdate=25 September 2015|work=[[DAWN.com]]|publisher=Salima Feerasta}}</ref>\n\nNaveen Qazi of ''Siddy Says'' rated the film as \"4.5 out of 5 stars\". He said, \"staunch religious views and conservative mind-set should be left at home\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Bangkok and brazen banters|url=http://www.siddysays.com/movie-review-jawani-phir-nahi-ani/|website=Siddy Says|publisher=Naveen Qazi|accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref> Momin Ali Munshi of ''Galaxy Lollywood'' rated the film 3.8 out of 5 stars and wrote, \"''Jawani Phir Nahi An''i is an outright commercial film which scores full marks on the entertainment meter\". He praised the performances of Saeed, Butt, Chaudhry, Abro and Gillani.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani ( Review): This laugh out loud riot is the definition of good commercial cinema|url=http://galaxylollywood.com/2015/09/23/jawani-phir-nahi-ani-review-this-laugh-out-loud-riot-is-the-definition-of-good-commercial-cinema/|website=Galaxy Lollywood|publisher=Momin Ali Munshi|accessdate=25 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\nThe film had a television premier on [[Eid al-Fitr]], 4 July 2016, on ARY Digital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/arydigital.tv/videos/world-tv-premiere-of-jawani-phir-nahi-ani-on-1st-day-of-eid-only-on-ary-digital/1284405404904026/|title=Jawani Phir Nahi Ani - World Tv Premiere|last=ARY Digital|date=2 July 2016|accessdate=4 July 2016|via=Facebook}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\nAt the [[2nd ARY Film Awards]], ''Jawani Phir Nahi Ani'' received twenty-nine nominations and won eighteen categories. At the [[15th Lux Style Awards]], the film won two awards from ten nominations.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:99%;\"  <!-- to use sortable requires eliminating all use of rowspan -->\n|-\n! width=\"2%\" scope=\"col\" | Year\n! width=\"20%\" scope=\"col\" | Ceremony\n! width=\"25%\" scope=\"col\" | Category\n! width=\"25%\" scope=\"col\" | Recipient\n! width=\"8%\" scope=\"col\" | Result\n! width=\"2%\" scope=\"col\" | Ref\n|-\n| rowspan=\"39\" | 2016\n| rowspan=\"29\" | [[2nd ARY Film Awards|ARY Film Awards]]\n| colspan=\"2\"  | [[ARY Film Award for Best Film Jury|Best Film Jury]]\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"29\" |<center><ref>{{cite web|title=The nominations for the ARY Film Awards are out, with many stunning debut actors, directors and musicians vying for the coveted awards.|url=http://arynews.tv/en/ary-film-awards-2016-nominations-out/|publisher=[[ARY News]]|date=7 February 2016|accessdate=7 February 2016}}</ref></center> \n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Director Jury|Best Director Jury]]\n| Nadeem Baig\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"  | [[ARY Film Award for Best Film|Best Film]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n| Nadeem Baig\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] \n| [[Humayun Saeed]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2|[[ARY Film Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| [[Mehwish Hayat]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Sohai Ali Abro]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3|[[ARY Film Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]] \n| [[Hamza Ali Abbasi]] \n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Ahmed Ali Butt]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Vasay Chaudhry]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[ARY Film Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| [[Aisha Khan]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Sarwat Gilani]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[ARY Film Award for Best Star Debut Male|Best Star Debut Male]] \n| Ahmed Ali Butt\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Vasay Chaudhry\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Star Debut Female|Best Star Debut Female]]\n| [[Sarwat Gilani]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[ARY Film Award for Best Actor in a Comic Role|Best Actor in a Comic Role]]\n| [[Bushra Ansari]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Ahmed Ali Butt\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Actor in a Negative Role|Best Actor in a Negative Role]]\n| [[Ismail Tara]]\n| {{nom}}\n|- \n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Female Playback Singer|Best Playback Singer - Female]]\n| Sana Zulfiqar\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Male Playback Singer|Best Playback Singer - Male]]\n| [[Mika Singh]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Story|Best Story]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | Vasay Chaudhry\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Dialogue|Best Dialogue]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Original Music|Best Original Music]]\n| [[Shani Arshad]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Action|Best Action]]\n| Viktor Krav \n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Choreography|Best Choreography]]\n| Shabina Khan\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]]\n| Nabila and Jahanzeb Qamar \n| {{won}}\n|- \n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Makeup and Hairstyling|Best Makeup and Hairstyling]]\n| Nabila\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[ARY Film Award for Best Editing|Best Editing]]\n| Rizwan AQ\n| {{won}}\n